# Baseline Project Conventions

## Stack
Next.js 14 App Router · TypeScript (strict) · SCSS Modules · Vitest + Testing Library · pnpm

## Folder Structure
- UI components → `src/components/ui/<name>/`
- Layout primitives → `src/components/layout/<name>/`
- Custom hooks → `src/hooks/`
- Pure utilities → `src/utils/`
- Shared types → `src/types/`
- Design tokens → `src/styles/tokens/` (SCSS variables)
- Theme (CSS custom props) → `src/styles/theme/`

## Path Alias
Always use `@/` for imports from `src/`. Never use relative `../../` traversals that cross folder boundaries.

```ts
// ✅
import { cn } from '@/utils/cn';
// ❌
import { cn } from '../../../utils/cn';
```

## TypeScript
- `strict: true` — no `any`, no non-null assertions without a comment explaining why
- Use `type` (never `interface`) for all type definitions
- Use `type` imports for type-only symbols: `import type { Foo } from './Foo'`
- Prop types stay in the component file; any type reused across files goes in `ComponentName.types.ts`
- Shared cross-component types live in `src/types/`

```ts
// ✅
type ButtonProps = { variant?: 'primary' | 'secondary' };

// ❌
interface ButtonProps { variant?: 'primary' | 'secondary' }
```

## Functions
- Use arrow functions everywhere — components, utilities, hooks, callbacks, event handlers
- Exception: Next.js page/layout default exports may use either style

```ts
// ✅
export const cn = (...classes: (string | undefined | null | false)[]): string =>
  classes.filter(Boolean).join(' ');

const handleClick = () => { ... };

// ❌
function cn(...classes) { ... }
function handleClick() { ... }
```

## Naming
- Components and their files: `PascalCase` (`Button`, `Button.tsx`)
- Hooks: `camelCase` prefixed with `use` (`useDisclosure`)
- Utilities: `camelCase` (`cn`, `truncate`)
- SCSS module files: `ComponentName.module.scss`
- Test files: `ComponentName.test.tsx` / `hookName.test.ts`
- Component-scoped types: `ComponentName.types.ts`
- Component-scoped utils: `ComponentName.utils.ts`

## Component Size & Reuse
- Keep components small and focused — if a component grows beyond ~100 lines, consider splitting
- Extract repeated UI patterns into shared components rather than duplicating JSX
- Avoid over-engineering: don't abstract until the pattern appears at least twice
- Move complex logic out of the component:
  - Pure calculations / data transforms → `ComponentName.utils.ts`
  - Stateful logic / side effects → a dedicated hook (`useComponentName.ts`)

## Exports
- Every component folder must have an `index.ts` barrel export
- All public symbols must be re-exported from `src/index.ts`

## Scripts
| Task | Command |
|------|---------|
| Dev server | `pnpm dev` |
| Tests | `pnpm test` |
| Lint | `pnpm lint` |
| Format | `pnpm format` |
